The American green kingfishers are the kingfisher genus Chloroceryle, which are native to tropical Central and South America, with one species extending north to south Texas.
Taxonomy and species
The genus Chloroceryle was introduced in 1848 by the German naturalist Johann Jakob Kaup. Kaup did not specify a type species but Richard Bowdler Sharpe designated the American pygmy kingfisher in 1871. The genus name combines the Ancient Greek khl≈çros meaning "green" with the genus Ceryle that was introduced by Friedrich Boie in 1828.
